sols_latex:
Using the hint, we see that

\begin{align*}
S\left( \begin{bmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{bmatrix} \right) = \begin{bmatrix} -y + z \\ x + y + z \\ -x - 2y \end{bmatrix} 
=  \begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ x  \\ -x  \end{bmatrix} +  \begin{bmatrix} -y  \\ y \\ -2y \end{bmatrix} +  \begin{bmatrix} z \\  z \\ 0 \end{bmatrix} 
=  x\begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 1  \\ -1  \end{bmatrix} +  y\begin{bmatrix} -1  \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{bmatrix} +  \begin{bmatrix} 1 \\  1 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

Using these as our column vectors, we arrive at

\begin{align*}
S = \begin{bmatrix} 0 & -1 & 1 \\ 1 & 1 & 1 \\ -1 & -2 & 0 \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

